    "Furthermore, the proposed scheme controls the verification attack by detecting the source of the poison content.",
    "However, a malicious user can store their invalid content as verified valid content in CS.",
    "Ghall et al. (2014a), Ghali et al. (2014b), added that the mitigation of CPA relies on the trust management of the network layer.",
    "The authors state that CPA are based on two primary factors: The lack of a clear interest ambiguity and no previous model of trust.",
    "• Ambiguous InterestsIn NDN routers, each interest consists of the name of the content that is interested without the PPKD that is a required field in an interest."
  ]
